IRS990.Desc: TO PROVIDE VARIOUS TYPES OF MENTAL HEALTH CARE SERVICES THROUGHOUT OCEAN COUNTY, NEW JERSEY. THESE SERVICES INCLUDE, BUT ARE NOT LIMITED TO, DIAGNOSIS, PSYCHOLOGICAL EVALUATION, PSYCHOTHERAPY, REHABILITATION, ETC.

SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE ORGANIZATION REGULARLY REVIEWS AND EVALUATES ITS TAX POSITIONS TAKEN IN PREVIOUSLY FILED INFORMATION RETURNS AND AS REFLECTED IN ITS FINANCIAL STATEMENTS, WITH REGARD TO ISSUES AFFECTING ITS TAX EXEMPT STATUS, UNRELATED BUSINESS INCOME, AND RELATED MATTERS. THE ORGANIZATION BELIEVES THAT IN THE EVENT OF AN EXAMINATION BY TAXING AUTHORITIES, THE ORGANIZATION'S POSITIONS WOULD PREVAIL BASED UPON THE TECHNICAL MERITS OF SUCH POSITIONS. THEREFORE, THE ORGANIZATION HAS CONCLUDED THAT NO TAX BENEFITS OR LIABILITIES ARE REQUIRED TO BE RECOGNIZED IN ACCORDANCE WITH THE PROVISIONS OF ACCOUNTING STANDARDS CODIFICATION ("ASC") SECTION 740, "ACCOUNTING FOR INCOME TAXES" (ASC 740).

PART IV, LINE 11F - INCOME TAXES - OMHS IS A NON-PROFIT ORGANIZATION, WHICH IS EXEMPT FROM FEDERAL INCOME TAXES UNDER INTERNAL REVENUE CODE SECTION 501(C)(3) AND STATE INCOME TAXES UNDER THE CHARITABLE REGISTRATION ACT. OMHS HAS BEEN CLASSIFIED BY THE INTERNAL REVENUE SERVICE AS OTHER THAN A PRIVATE FOUNDATION. THE ORGANIZATION HAS ADOPTED THE ACCOUNTING STANDARD RELATING TO ACCOUNTING FOR UNCERTAINTY IN INCOME TAXES. THE STANDARD CLARIFIES THE ACCOUNTING FOR UNCERTAINTY IN INCOME TAXES RECOGNIZED IN AN ENTERPRISE'S FINANCIAL STATEMENTS AND PRESCRIBES A RECOGNITION THRESHOLD AND MEASUREMENT PROCESS FOR FINANCIAL STATEMENT RECOGNITION AND MEASUREMENT OF A TAX POSITION TAKEN OR EXPECTED TO BE TAKEN IN A TAX RETURN. THE STANDARD ALSO PROVIDES GUIDANCE ON DE-RECOGNITION, CLASSIFICATION, INTEREST AND PENALTIES, ACCOUNTING IN INTERIM PERIODS, DISCLOSURE, AND TRANSITION. BASED ON ITS EVALUATION, THE ORGANIZTION HAS CONCLUDED THAT THERE ARE NO SIGNIFICANT UNCERTAIN TAX POSITIONS REQUIRING RECOGNITION IN THE FINANCIAL STATEMENTS. THERE ARE NO INCOME TAX RELATED PENALTIES OR INTEREST FOR THE PERIODS PRESENTED IN THESE FINANCIAL STATEMENTS.
THE 990 WILL BE COPIED AND DISTRIBUTED TO MEMBERS BEFORE THE NEXT BOARD MEETING, WHERE IT WILL BE DISCUSSED AND APPROVED BY THE BOARD.

1. EMPLOYEES ARE REQUIRED TO DISCLOSE ANNUALLY ANY CONFLICT OF INTEREST. 2. THE ORGANIZATION REGULARLY AND CONSISTENTLY MONITORS ENFORCEMENT. 3. THE CODE OF CONDUCT POLICY IS DISTRIBUTED AND SIGNED UPON EMPLOYMENT AND ANNUALLY THEREAFTER.
SALARY SCALES ARE DETERMINED BY THE CEO AND APPROVED BY THE BOARD.
